    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%" height=3D28><FONT size=3D2>37,544 =
KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%" height=3D28><FONT =
size=3D2>soffice.bin &amp;=20
      soffice.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT size=3D2>Impress</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>44,788 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT size=3D2>soffice.bin &amp;=20
      soffice.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT size=3D2>Base</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>36,036 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT size=3D2>soffice.bin &amp;=20
      soffice.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT size=3D2>Word</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>9,812 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT =
size=3D2>WinWord.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT size=3D2>Excel</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>7,102 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT =
size=3D2>Excel.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT =
size=3D2>PowerPoint</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>6,884 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT =
size=3D2>PowerPNT.exe</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"17%"><FONT size=3D2>Access</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"20%"><FONT size=3D2>7,302 KB</FONT></TD>
    <TD align=3Dright width=3D"30%"><FONT=20
size=3D2>MSAccess.exe</FONT></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
<P>As you can see, OpenOffice.org takes up a lot more RAM to load than =
Microsoft=20
Office applications.&nbsp; While it=E2=80=99s true that the =
OpenOffice.org applications=20
will share memory with each other, Microsoft Office applications will =
also share=20
RAM with each other.&nbsp; RAM consumption rises rapidly for both =
Microsoft=20
Office and OpenOffice.org as soon as data is loaded, OpenOffice.org =
still takes=20
significantly more RAM than Microsoft Office.&nbsp; The difference in =
memory=20
utilization is shown in both the bare application comparison and even =
more so=20
with the large 16-sheet spreadsheet loaded.&nbsp; Also note that the =
Base=20
application requires Java Runtime Engine for many of its features so the =
RAM=20
requirement shoots even higher.</P>
<P>I=E2=80=99ve emailed OpenOffice.org last month asking them if they =
would like to=20
explain the severe performance difference but I haven=E2=80=99t heard =
anything back=20
yet.</P>
<DIV class=3D"bloggerDesc clear">
